\mathcal{F}_{Q;r,q}=\{\gamma=\frac{m}{n} | 0\leq m \leq n \leq Q, \gcd(m,n)=1, n \equiv r \mod q, \gcd(r,q)=1\}
\# \mathcal{F}_{Q}
=\varphi(1)+\varphi(2)+\varphi(3)+\cdots+\varphi(Q)
=\frac{3Q^2}{\pi^2}+O(Q\log Q)
Q\rightarrow \infty
